    "summary": "On January 16, 2016, a Sr. Subsea Engineer inadvertently actuated the Riser Connector unlock button instead of the POCV Override button while lining up the choke manifold for BOP offline testing. This caused the LMRP to disconnect from the BOP, resulting in the release of 350 barrels of Calcium Chloride drilling mud into the Gulf of Mexico. Estimated damage was $47,500.",
